1
00:01:31,390 --> 00:01:34,850
[Silent Tides]

2
00:01:35,210 --> 00:01:38,000
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,120
I can't guarantee

4
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,770
that I'll be able to borrow it,

5
00:01:40,770 --> 00:01:43,100
but I'll definitely give it my all anyway.

6
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:45,400
As for Banco Nacional Ultramarino,

7
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,259
I'll find a way out.

8
00:01:46,259 --> 00:01:47,039
We're short of time,

9
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:48,500
so I won't go into details.

10
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:52,080
But right now, my biggest concern is
neither of these.

11
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:53,390
After this morning's incident,

12
00:01:53,390 --> 00:01:54,870
the Japanese must now suspect

13
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:56,229
that the HSBC treasurer

14
00:01:56,229 --> 00:01:57,050
disclosed the secret

15
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:59,509
of the forcibly issued HKD
before his death.

16
00:01:59,860 --> 00:02:01,920
The entire rubber business is a scam.

17
00:02:02,470 --> 00:02:04,480
Unless the Japanese have their doubts
completely erased,

18
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,220
whatever trap we set this afternoon,

19
00:02:06,220 --> 00:02:08,310
they're unlikely to fall for it easily.

20
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:09,639
So this is the key issue.

21
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,070
How about

22
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,420
I give it a try?

23
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,000
Xian,

24
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,800
what's your plan?

25
00:02:24,130 --> 00:02:26,540
If we want the Japanese to believe
that the treasurer didn't leak anything,

26
00:02:26,540 --> 00:02:29,100
we must take the initiative
to give them an answer.

27
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,720
And only one person is suited

28
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:32,950
to give them this answer.

29
00:02:33,430 --> 00:02:34,010
Who is it?

30
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,990
A person who should be kept far away
from this conflict

31
00:02:37,990 --> 00:02:39,140
and kept safe

32
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:40,780
from any harm.

33
00:02:57,660 --> 00:02:58,520
Please come in.

34
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,020
Dr. Ke.

35
00:03:02,510 --> 00:03:03,380
Mr. Rodrigues.

36
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,550
What brings you here?

37
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:06,930
I'm here

38
00:03:07,210 --> 00:03:08,530
to tell you a story.

39
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:24,810
Xian.

40
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,329
Yinwan.

41
00:03:26,730 --> 00:03:27,530
What's wrong?

42
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,590
Why did you suddenly call me out?

43
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:32,329
Have a seat.

44
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,590
I called you here

45
00:03:47,110 --> 00:03:48,640
because I wanted to tell you

46
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,120
that I've seen your brother.

47
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:55,480
You've seen my brother?

48
00:03:56,370 --> 00:03:57,620
When and where?

49
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:00,370
Yesterday.

50
00:04:01,130 --> 00:04:01,840
In Macau.

51
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:07,420
[Hai Ho's Hall]

52
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:08,480
You mean

53
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,770
you want to borrow

54
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,970
all the funds of my Tai Ho Brotherhood?

55
00:04:16,970 --> 00:04:17,769
Master Sanhe.

56
00:04:18,339 --> 00:04:19,399
In the past,

57
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:22,120
I, Ma Wanqi, would have given you my word

58
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,240
that your money

59
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,700
would be returned in full.

60
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,720
But this time,

61
00:04:27,260 --> 00:04:28,920
I cannot make any guarantees.

62
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,120
Because once the plan fails,

63
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:37,190
the 4 major banks of Chinese merchants
will face total ruin,

64
00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:39,460
with both Tai Fung Bank and Hengfengyu

65
00:04:40,210 --> 00:04:42,140
declaring bankruptcy on the spot.

66
00:04:42,330 --> 00:04:44,590
I'm not telling this story for idle chat,

67
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:45,750
but because this story

68
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:47,280
is directly related to you.

69
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,070
Because you not only know

70
00:04:49,070 --> 00:04:50,400
the protagonist of this story,

71
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,900
but all the hardships he has endured

72
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,560
stemmed from the faith

73
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,930
he kept with you.

74
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,020
You mean

75
00:04:59,290 --> 00:05:00,830
my brother not only issued
Hong Kong dollars

76
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:02,490
for the Japanese in Hong Kong,

77
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:05,010
but now he has specifically come to Macau

78
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,870
to continue covering up for them?

79
00:05:07,570 --> 00:05:08,890
This batch of forcibly issued HKD

80
00:05:08,890 --> 00:05:10,620
has a huge impact on the market.

81
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,800
That's why the Japanese

82
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,720
are using your brother's identity

83
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:16,480
to deceive Macau's merchants and banks,

84
00:05:16,690 --> 00:05:18,600
so that they can maintain

85
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:20,620
their control over HKD
in today's exchange.

86
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:21,430
But both Macau's financial industry

87
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:23,070
and its citizens

88
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:24,310
are consequently

89
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:26,450
suffering tremendous losses.

90
00:05:27,980 --> 00:05:30,240
Then why didn't you expose him directly?

91
00:05:30,340 --> 00:05:31,570
Didn't the treasurer

92
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:32,940
tell you the truth before he died?

93
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:34,370
Why didn't you

94
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:36,010
tell the citizens of Macau directly?

95
00:05:36,010 --> 00:05:37,510
We're bankers.

96
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,240
If we were to expose this,

97
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:41,020
few people would believe us.

98
00:05:41,030 --> 00:05:42,450
Our credibility is
nowhere near the level of trust

99
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:45,450
placed in your brother,
the Chief Accountant of HSBC.

100
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,290
That is to say,

101
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:54,520
because of my brother's lies,

102
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,190
many citizens of Macau

103
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:58,140
are now being deceived by the Japanese

104
00:05:58,140 --> 00:05:59,610
and are losing their life savings

105
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:00,840
while being kept completely in the dark.

106
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,640
Is that right?

107
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:05,130
Yes.

108
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,140
What exactly did the treasurer tell you
before he died?

109
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,290
How much is this batch of
Hong Kong dollars in total?

110
00:06:17,290 --> 00:06:19,490
And what do the Japanese plan to do next?

111
00:06:22,010 --> 00:06:23,470
Do you really want to know?

112
00:06:26,170 --> 00:06:27,300
Someone must expose

113
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,760
my brother's lies.

114
00:06:29,710 --> 00:06:32,110
Someone must make amends for his mistakes.

115
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,920
Even though I can't compensate
for everything,

116
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:38,050
at least I can reduce some of the losses.

117
00:06:38,050 --> 00:06:39,380
Every little bit helps.

118
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,000
Okay.

119
00:06:45,570 --> 00:06:47,030
I'll tell you everything.

120
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:58,000
What are you doing?

121
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:19,090
Since Banco Nacional Ultramarino
can't honor its commitment,

122
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:21,730
then I, Rodrigues, will honor it.

123
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:25,590
How much Hong Kong dollars
does the bank have left?

124
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:31,290
Withdraw all sell orders.
I'll buy them all.

125
00:07:38,810 --> 00:07:41,010
There are sell orders for 7 million HKD.

126
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:42,180
Banco Nacional Ultramarino

127
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:43,940
just added sell orders for 7 million HKD.

128
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:45,270
Combined with this morning's sell orders,

129
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:47,730
that brings the total
to exactly 15 million.

130
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,650
Mr. Lin.

131
00:08:04,030 --> 00:08:06,030
What I brought is heavy.

132
00:08:06,050 --> 00:08:08,200
Ask all your men to come out and help.

133
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:12,740
Be careful.

134
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:13,620
[Tai Fung Bank]

135
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:14,350
Slow down, buddy.

136
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:15,150
Slow down.

137
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:15,850
Be careful.

138
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:16,300
Here.

139
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,070
Hand it over.

140
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:18,220
[Ho Yee]

141
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:19,100
Be careful.

142
00:08:19,130 --> 00:08:20,190
Catch it. Catch it.

143
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,190
Be careful.

144
00:08:21,210 --> 00:08:21,680
Here.

145
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,540
Hand it over.

146
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:26,480
Quan, what's wrong with you?

147
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,300
[Tai Fung Bank]

148
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:27,890
I'm sorry, Mr. Ma.

149
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:28,810
Hurry up and pick them up.

150
00:08:28,810 --> 00:08:29,510
After counting,

151
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:31,330
they still needs to be delivered
to the exchange for the margin.

152
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:32,059
Understood.

153
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:34,630
He's gone.

154
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:36,919
Quan.

155
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:37,409
Yes.

156
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,289
Lock the box with bricks in the vault.

157
00:08:39,289 --> 00:08:40,820
Take the rest of the money to the exchange
as soon as possible.

158
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:41,549
Understood.

159
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:42,929
Hurry up.

160
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:51,780
General Manager.

161
00:08:51,980 --> 00:08:54,160
HKD has already fallen below 2.7 dollars.

162
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:56,020
The Chinese merchants
show no signs of buying.

163
00:08:56,020 --> 00:08:57,620
What should we do now?

164
00:09:00,070 --> 00:09:01,230
You spy!

165
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:04,130
How did you collude
with those Chinese merchants?

166
00:09:04,130 --> 00:09:04,990
Tell me!

167
00:09:07,590 --> 00:09:08,520
Mr. Ogata.

168
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:12,280
Now is not the time
to deal with this spy.

169
00:09:12,490 --> 00:09:14,380
Let's hurry and sell off our holdings.

170
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:17,520
So Lee Kong Chian's rubber business is
a scam.

171
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,130
Am I right?

172
00:09:20,290 --> 00:09:21,760
Listen up, everyone!

173
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,810
Don't trust HKD anymore.

174
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:26,060
If you have Hong Kong dollars,
sell them off.

175
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:27,250
The news spread by the Japanese

176
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:28,620
is all fake.

177
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:30,560
This is their conspiracy.

178
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,740
Do you all remember

179
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:34,580
the news in the paper a few days ago

180
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:36,080
about the HSBC treasurer

181
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,580
who died in Macau?

182
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:39,150
-Yes.
-Yes.

183
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,390
When the HSBC treasurer died,

184
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:42,270
I was right there on the scene.

185
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:43,500
Before he died,

186
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,470
he revealed a shocking truth to us.

187
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,730
Was that woman really there at the time?

188
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:49,940
Yes.

189
00:09:51,470 --> 00:09:52,570
Oh, no.

190
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,150
The truth about HKD has been exposed.

191
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:04,090
The so-called newly issued
Hong Kong dollars by HSBC

192
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:05,630
were actually stolen by the Japanese

193
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:08,070
from HSBC's vault.

194
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,550
There are no reserve funds at all.

195
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:11,090
They're equivalent to
a pile of waste paper.

196
00:10:11,090 --> 00:10:12,270
And the news says

197
00:10:12,270 --> 00:10:13,790
that the total for this batch of HKD
is only 10 million.

198
00:10:13,790 --> 00:10:15,790
That is an out-and-out lie.

199
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:18,320
The actual amount issued far exceeds
what was reported in the news.

200
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:20,240
Moreover, the Japanese will choose a date

201
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:22,790
to invalidate all these Hong Kong dollars.

202
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:25,940
-They're all exposed. Oh, no.
-If you have Hong Kong dollars,
sell them off.

203
00:10:25,940 --> 00:10:26,980
Now everything is ruined.

204
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,030
Is it true?

205
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:29,680
Who on earth is this person?

206
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:30,800
I don't know.

207
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:32,860
Isn't it Miss Qiao Yinwan?

208
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:33,860
You know her?

209
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:35,320
She's the sister of Qiao Renyu,

210
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,370
the Chief Accountant of HSBC.

211
00:10:36,370 --> 00:10:37,910
Qiao Yinwan, a violinist.

212
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:39,390
Besides, these Hong Kong dollars

213
00:10:39,390 --> 00:10:40,740
were issued by her brother.

214
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:42,510
What she says must be true.

215
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,410
Hurry and sell off
all your Hong Kong dollars, everyone.

216
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:47,260
Yes, hurry and sell off
your Hong Kong dollars.

217
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:49,520
Come and sell off your Hong Kong dollars.

218
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:50,710
Inform the traders.

219
00:10:50,730 --> 00:10:53,110
Sell them off!
Sell all the Hong Kong dollars off!

220
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:53,510
Yes.

221
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:02,960
What did you say?

222
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,160
What's wrong?

223
00:11:04,180 --> 00:11:05,310
The trader reported

224
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:06,080
that Banco Nacional Ultramarino

225
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,050
just withdrew all their sell orders

226
00:11:08,050 --> 00:11:09,820
and started buying instead.

227
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:11,000
What?

228
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,870
Miss Qiao, I'm the Chairman
of Tai Fung Bank.

229
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:16,700
You just said the amount
of Hong Kong dollars issued is incorrect.

230
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:17,750
Then what is

231
00:11:17,780 --> 00:11:18,890
the exact amount?

232
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,540
It's exactly 40 million.

233
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:21,750
Forty million?

234
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:22,740
That much?

235
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:23,530
You also said

236
00:11:23,530 --> 00:11:25,140
that the Japanese want to invalidate HKD.

237
00:11:25,140 --> 00:11:27,250
Then what will they use to replace it?

238
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,010
After the Japanese

239
00:11:28,010 --> 00:11:29,740
sell all these Hong Kong dollars,

240
00:11:29,740 --> 00:11:31,130
they'll force HSBC

241
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:32,100
to issue new Hong Kong dollars.

242
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,580
By then, all the old Hong Kong dollars

243
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:36,240
can only be exchanged at a discount
for new ones.

244
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:40,070
Hurry and sell off your Hong Kong dollars!

245
00:11:40,490 --> 00:11:42,660
What nonsense is she talking about?

246
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:44,870
General Manager.

247
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:47,030
This woman claimed
to be revealing the truth,

248
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,870
but what she said about the amount
of Hong Kong dollars issued

249
00:11:48,870 --> 00:11:51,140
and the follow-up measures
is completely wrong.

250
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:52,400
What she said

251
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:56,860
couldn't possibly come from
the HSBC treasurer.

252
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:00,860
It was totally fabricated.

253
00:12:03,310 --> 00:12:04,090
Report!

254
00:12:04,830 --> 00:12:05,560
What is it?

255
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:09,420
Our informant at Tai Fung Bank reported

256
00:12:09,420 --> 00:12:11,370
that Huang Sanhe just escorted
Tai Ho Brotherhood's

257
00:12:11,370 --> 00:12:12,370
cash reserves

258
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:13,960
into Tai Fung Bank.

259
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,370
Tai Ho Brotherhood?

260
00:12:15,390 --> 00:12:17,480
It's the largest smuggling gang
in the area.

261
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:18,810
It's very powerful

262
00:12:18,830 --> 00:12:21,760
and is also in cahoots
with those Chinese merchants.

263
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,030
How do you know

264
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:27,100
he was escorting
Tai Ho Brotherhood's cash reserves?

265
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,780
All the boxes have the characters
"Ho Yee" on them.

266
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:31,450
Those are the cash boxes
for the gang's savings.

267
00:12:31,570 --> 00:12:33,950
Huang Sanhe brought
20 to 30 boxes this time.

268
00:12:33,950 --> 00:12:35,980
It seems that he's betting
everything he has.

269
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:38,440
You mean
there are dozens of boxes of dollars?

270
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,480
Not just that.

271
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:41,740
Huang Sanhe also brought many gold bars.

272
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:45,470
Qiao Renyu's sister was spreading lies
in public.

273
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,620
What is the exact amount
of Hong Kong dollars issued?

274
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:49,170
It's exactly 40 million.

275
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:51,320
Hurry and sell off all your
Hong Kong dollars.

276
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:54,000
Yes, hurry and sell off
your Hong Kong dollars.

277
00:12:54,020 --> 00:12:57,080
Banco Nacional Ultramarino
withdrew sell orders and started buying.

278
00:12:57,080 --> 00:13:00,160
Tai Fung Bank also secretly transferred in
a large sum of money.

